All Classes

Class Description
Actor
Actor is the base abstract class for all child nodes to be displayed in the scene graph of the Frogger game.
Animal
The Animal class provides a playable character that can handle key inputs from the user.
Animal.DeathType
An enumeration describing various death types and the number of unique images in the corresponding animation.
BackgroundImage
BackgroundImage is a class that provides an ImageView that displays an Image with dimensions to fit the application window.
Car
The Car class provides a Car obstacle of varying colours in the Frogger game.
Car.CarTypes
An enumeration of different types of Cars and their corresponding labels.
Digit
The Digit class provides a displayable image of a digit.
End
The End class provides a displayable image of the end goal of the Frogger game.
Fireball
The Fireball class provides a Fireball obstacle that has an animation in the Frogger game.
Highscore
The Highscore class provides a way for the Frogger game to store highscores with a name attached to a score value.
HighscoreController
The HighscoreController class provides utilities for determining a whether a new score is a new highscore, and uses a HighscoreLoader for reading and writing a list of Highscores to a file.
HighscoreLoader
The HighscoreLoader class provides the utilities of reading and writing a list of Highscores to a .csv file in the highscores directory.
InfoPage
InfoPage is a class that provides a info page screen for the Frogger game.
Level
Level is the base abstract class which all Frogger levels must be a subclass of.
Level.Section
An enumeration that specifies each row of the Frogger level and its corresponding y-coordinate.
LevelEight
LevelEight is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelFactory
LevelFactory is an abstract class solely used for returning instances of subclasses of Level.
LevelFive
LevelFive is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelFour
LevelFour is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelNine
LevelNine is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelOne
LevelOne is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelRandom
LevelRandom is a class that creates a Level, with procedurally generated child nodes, for the Frogger game to use.
LevelSelect
The LevelSelect class provides a screen for which a user can click preset NavButtons to navigate to the corresponding Level destinations using Navigation.
LevelSeven
LevelSeven is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelSix
LevelSix is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelThree
LevelThree is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
LevelTwo
LevelTwo is a class that creates a custom Level for the Frogger game to use.
Log
The Log class provides a Log platform of varying sizes in the Frogger game.
Log.LogTypes
An enumeration of different types of Logs and their corresponding labels and sizes.
Main
The Main class is the entry point the Frogger application lifecycle and performs what a JavaFX Application does.
MainMenu
The MainMenu class provides a preset starting screen with NavButtons for navigating to the InfoPage and LevelSelect destinations.
MusicPlayer
The MusicPlayer class is used for loading and playing a sound file indefinitely.
NavButton
The NavButton class provides a displayable clickable button which on click, calls Navigation to navigate to a specified destination.
NavController
The NavController is a controller class used for manipulating a JavaFX scene graph.
Navigation
The Navigation class provides utilities for switching between screens in the Frogger application by using a NavController.
Obstacle
The Obstacle class is the abstract class which all Frogger obstacles(nodes that cannot be stood on by the Frogger) must be a subclass of.
Platform
The Platform class is the abstract class which all Frogger platforms(nodes that can be stood on by the Frogger) must be a subclass of.
SinkingPlatform
The SinkingPlatform class is the abstract class which all Frogger platforms(nodes that can be stood on by the Frogger) that 'sink' below the surface must be a subclass of.
Truck
The Truck class provides a Truck obstacle of varying sizes in the Frogger game.
Truck.TruckTypes
An enumeration of different types of Trucks and their corresponding sizes.
Turtle
The Turtle class provides a Turtle platform that has a swimming animation in the Frogger game.
WetTurtle
The WetTurtle class provides a WetTurtle platform that has a diving animation in the Frogger game.
World
World is the base abstract class to be extended by all branch nodes in the JavaFX scene graph of the Frogger game.
